SUMMARY:Tools\, MCP and Agents with LangChain4j
DESCRIPTION:Microsoft Reactor Toronto\nMove from "text generator" to "acti
 on taker." You'll expose Java methods as tools using @Tool annotations and
  watch the AI chain them automatically with the ReAct pattern. Then you'll
  explore Model Context Protocol (MCP)—an open standard for AI-to-tool co
 mmunication—and build a Supervisor Agent that dynamically orchestrates s
 ub-agents to read files\, analyze content\, and summarize results\n\nPre-r
 equisites:\nCheck out the LangChain4j beginners series: https://aka.ms/lan
 gchain4j-for-beginners\nSign up for an Azure free trial: https://aka.ms/Az
 ureFreeTrialDevRelAll
